PRACTICAL FROM SCRATCH

STEP 1 — Launch EC2 Instance

Use free tier EC2.

Choose AMI

Amazon Linux 2

Instance type

t2.micro

Security group rules

Allow:

SSH 22 My IP

HTTP 80 Anywhere

Why these ports?

Port 22

SSH access for terminal login.

Port 80

HTTP access for browser.

Without port 80:

site not opening

STEP 2 — Attach IAM role (very important, students often miss this)
Attach EC2 role with:

AmazonS3ReadOnlyAccess

Why needed?

Without IAM role:

aws s3 cp → Access Denied

STEP 3 — Connect to EC2

ssh -i your-key.pem ec2-user@PUBLIC-IP

Example:

ssh -i lab.pem ec2-user@13.48.xx.xx

Common beginner mistake

Wrong username:

Wrong:

ubuntu

Correct for Amazon Linux:

ec2-user

STEP 4 — Install web server

Inside EC2:

sudo yum update -y

sudo yum install httpd -y

sudo systemctl start httpd

sudo systemctl enable httpd

Verify Apache running

sudo systemctl status httpd

You must see:

active (running)

Why Apache?

Apache serves files placed in:

/var/www/html

to browser automatically.

STEP 5 — Create application locally

On laptop:

mkdir myapp

cd myapp

Create HTML file

echo "<h1>DevOps Lab Program 7</h1>" > index.html

Verify

cat index.html

Output:

<h1>DevOps Lab Program 7</h1>

STEP 6 — Create deployment artifact

Zip file

zip myapp.zip index.html

Theory

Artifact means:

deployable packaged file

Source code = editable

Artifact = deployable package

STEP 7 — Create S3 bucket

Create bucket in Amazon S3

Example:

myapp-lab-demo

Upload artifact

Upload:

myapp.zip

Why S3?

S3 acts as:

central artifact storage

STEP 8 — Install AWS CLI if missing

Inside EC2:

sudo yum install aws-cli -y

Verify AWS CLI

aws --version

STEP 9 — Download artifact from S3

Inside EC2:

aws s3 cp s3://myapp-lab-demo/myapp.zip .

If Access Denied

Cause:

IAM role missing.

STEP 10 — Install unzip if missing

sudo yum install unzip -y

STEP 11 — Extract artifact

unzip myapp.zip

Verify file

ls

Must show:

index.html

STEP 12 — Deploy to Apache folder

sudo cp index.html /var/www/html/

Why this folder?

Apache default website root:

/var/www/html

STEP 13 — Verify deployment

Open browser:

http://EC2-PUBLIC-IP

Expected output

<h1>DevOps Lab Program 7</h1>

STEP 14 — Simulate second deployment

Change local file:

echo "<h1>Version 2 Success</h1>" > index.html

zip myapp.zip index.html

Upload again to S3.

Download again in EC2

aws s3 cp s3://myapp-lab-demo/myapp.zip .

unzip -o myapp.zip

sudo cp index.html /var/www/html/

Refresh browser

Now:

<h1>Version 2 Success</h1>

Connect to CodeDeploy concept

Normally AWS CodeDeploy uses:

version: 0.0

os: linux

files:

 - source: /

 destination: /var/www/html

Meaning

source

Artifact files

destination

Server deployment folder
